The matrix was constructed using the WinClada program (

) and was exported to program TNT (

) where searches were conducted under equal and implied weights with different values of 
K
(from 1 to 10). In the implied weight strategy, the ideal weights of the characters are evaluated together with the tree search process (

). This last approach favors the phylogenetic signal of characters that have fewer homoplasies (

), resulting in a hypothesis that minimizes the total amount of homoplasy in the data and that supplies data with higher resolution.

